# Master Traceability Table ([PROJECT_NAME] - Lean)

Read when: changing entrypoints, function chains, side effects, or smoke evidence.
Skip when: routine local edits do not affect pathways.

Purpose: canonical pathway map for Tier B/C reliability without forcing it into every startup read.

## Path ID Format
- `[TYPE]-[COMPONENT]-[NUMBER]`
- Types: `UI`, `API-CS`, `API-HT`, `CRON`, `EDIT`, `WEB`, `JOB`

## Traceability Rules
- Every active entrypoint or pathway must have a Path ID row.
- Every Path ID must have smoke or contract coverage status:
  - `Automated`,
  - `Manual`, or
  - `N/A` with rationale.
- Update touched Path IDs in the same change when pathways change.

